quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Get Content[/h1]

There are several methods for manipulating the content of  HTML elements via jQuery. 
The[b] html()[/b] method is used to get the content of the selected element, including the HTML markup. 
[b]For example:[/b]
[b]HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<p>
  JQuery is <b>fun</b>
</p>[/code]
[b]JS:[/b] [code format="js" codeId="1106"]$(function() {
  var val = $("p").html();
  alert(val);
});
// alerts "JQuery is <b>fun</b>"[/code]
Notice, that the HTML markup (the <b> tags) is also returned,
If you need only the text content, without the HTML markup, you can use the [b]text()[/b] method: [code format="js" codeId="1107"]$(function() {
  var val = $("p").text();
  alert(val);
});
// alerts "JQuery is fun"[/code]
[note]The [b]html()[/b] and [b]text()[/b] methods can be used for all HTML elements that can contain content. [/note]

quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to change the content of the paragraphs with id="demo" to "<b>Hi</b>" maintaining the HTML markup.
[!raw!]
$(function() {
  $("{0}").{1}("<b>Hi</b>");
});
